It should also be noted that hentai character psychology is completely different than real life psychology. Which is fine, because fantasy. But in real life the thinking in this story (and most other hentai stories, frankly) would be unhealthy and very atypical.

The only reason why I bring this stuff up is because some people in the comments think this would be a cool thing to happen to them in real life. Dude, it would not go down this way in real life. Sorry. And some people in the comments seem to think this is wrong. Well, that's a larger argument with different takes but the prevailing opinion in some corners, I think, and one that I generally agree with, is that this probably doesn't hurt anyone. I don't think this stuff is wrong. Consent and age and stuff flat out don't matter for drawings (it doesn't mean you can't be weirded out or it's wrong if you are). Now, if this was real life child porn, that would be entirely different, but it's not, so whatever.

Morally, it's wrong whether it's incest or not, because the kids are being molested. It doesn't matter if the kids enjoy it or not; they're not old enough or developed enough mentally to be able to consent. In real life the issue arises in most incest cases because of consent issues and power dynamics, with the biological offspring aspect being a lesser concern. It's not morally an issue if a brother and sister in their 40s are doing it; weird, sure, but not wrong. But most of the time it's an older relative taking advantage of a younger one. This is predatory behavior.

In this case I would say the dad is less at fault than the mom because it wasn't premeditated, but it was still irresponsible of him and would still be bad on his part if he continued. The mom was straight up grooming her children.

All of this IS negated by the fact that it's a comic IMO. Morality doesn't matter here. I like this comic, myself. But we shouldn't pretend or wish that it's analogous to real life.
